blog.description: Most of the comics I read are Marvels from 1984. Every time I read a comic, I post a comment. That's pretty much it.

title: Colorado Caper!
body:
Spider-Man and the Incredible Hulk

More silliness designed to sell clothes.

  • Advertising supplement given away with newspapers. Sponsored by May D&F department stores.
  • Saturday Morning Cartoon Logic: All of it! Every word. If all Marvel Comics were aimed at children, they would be like this.

5/10

blog.name: fuckyeahx-23
blog.title: Target X
blog.description:
X-23 is the product of a top-secret project that attempted to recreate the original Weapon X. Cloned from a damaged DNA sample of Wolverine, X-23 was programmed to be the perfect killing machine.

She goes by Laura Kinney, a name given to her by her genetic creator/surrogate mother, Sarah Kinney.

Her official X-Men codename - before Wolverine - was Talon.

X-23 was created by Craig Kyle and Chris Yost, and first appeared on X-Men: Evolution.

If we post your art and you want it credited differently/taken down, please message us.

NSFW tags: #seX-23 and #sniktcest

summary:
Playing with the idea of other Spidermen from other cartoons interacting with the Ultimates.
This is Peter Parker from the...
body:
Playing with the idea of other Spidermen from other cartoons interacting with the Ultimates.

This is Peter Parker from the Amazing Spider-Man series. I’d imagine he’d be a bit put off with idea of others knowing so much about him as well as being a team player.

The team would be struggling to the idea of an older Peter, a married Peter.

The Web Warriors will forever dub him, “Daddy Longlegs.”

Peter eventually plays nice, or at least, nice enough to play with others until Madame Web is able to find him and send him back home.

(It may not be clear, but the “twink” they’re talking about is their Peter. It amazes them that this Peter isn’t a twink..)
